  \sum_{n=0}^\infty \left(\frac{\alpha}{\pi}\right)^{2n} I_{2n+2} = \int_0^1dx\,\sum_{n=0}^\infty \left(\frac{\alpha}{\pi}\right)^{2n} {\cal P}_n(x,0) = \int_0^1dx\, {\cal G}(\alpha,x,0)    =\int_0^1dx\frac{1}{2 \sqrt{1-\alpha ^2}}\left[\left(\frac{1-x}{x}\right)^{c}+\left(\frac{1-x}{x }\right)^{-c}\right] = \frac{\sin^{-1}\alpha}{\alpha\sqrt{1-\alpha^2}}  = \sum_{n=0}^\infty (2\alpha)^{2n} B(n+1,n+1)\ . 
